# Spring Boot Integration Testing

## Full Context Tests
- `@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = RANDOM_PORT)` for full integration tests
- Use `TestRestTemplate` or `WebTestClient` for HTTP calls
- Test real request/response cycles through the full stack

## Testcontainers
- `@Testcontainers` + `@Container` for database and service containers
- `@ServiceConnection` (Spring Boot 3.1+ / 4.x) for automatic connection configuration
- Shared containers via `static` fields for performance
- Use `@DynamicPropertySource` for custom property injection

## WireMock
- Stub external HTTP services with WireMock
- `@WireMockTest` or embedded `WireMockServer`
- Verify expected interactions with external services

## Test Data
- `@Sql` for database setup/teardown scripts
- `@Transactional` on test classes for automatic rollback
- Test fixtures: realistic but minimal data sets

## Naming Convention
- Suffix: `*IntegrationTest.java` or `*IT.java`
- Configure Maven Failsafe plugin to run `*IT.java` separately

## Performance
- Share expensive containers across test classes
- Use `@DirtiesContext` sparingly -- only when context state is corrupted

